WEBVTT

00:06.267 --> 00:09.270
[lively jazz music]

00:09.270 --> 00:12.490
♪ ♪

00:12.490 --> 00:13.926
Our problems are sexual.

00:13.926 --> 00:15.406
[sighs]
Let me tell it, Moe.

00:15.406 --> 00:18.235
So tell it, but you only
give your point of view.

00:18.235 --> 00:21.195
Last year, our sex life
came to a halt.

00:21.195 --> 00:22.979
It was never great.

00:22.979 --> 00:25.025
Do not interrupt me,
Moe.

00:25.025 --> 00:28.419
It went from three times
a week to twice to once,

00:28.419 --> 00:31.074
and then, bingo,
he stops trying.

00:31.074 --> 00:32.336
Mm-hmm.

00:32.336 --> 00:34.295
So since he's a man

00:34.295 --> 00:35.905
with a normal
sex drive...

00:35.905 --> 00:37.124
A strong sex drive.

00:37.124 --> 00:38.777
...No more than normal.

00:38.777 --> 00:40.779
I got a little
suspicious.

00:40.779 --> 00:43.434
And then I notice
his credit card bills.

00:44.914 --> 00:46.307
- She snooped.
- Mm!

00:46.307 --> 00:48.352
You damn right
I snooped.

00:48.352 --> 00:50.006
So I see this
credit card bill

00:50.006 --> 00:52.835
with escort services,
right?

00:52.835 --> 00:55.229
Massage parlors.
So I confronted him.

00:55.229 --> 00:56.447
- And I admitted it.
- Mm-hmm.

00:56.447 --> 00:58.101
Those encounters
excited me,

00:58.101 --> 01:01.322
and to get into bed
with my wife no longer did.

01:01.322 --> 01:03.367
Did you ever hear
of such a thing?

01:03.367 --> 01:05.021
Go on.

01:05.021 --> 01:07.850
So we came to you.
[exhales]

01:07.850 --> 01:10.374
You listened to us,
and you said,

01:10.374 --> 01:12.333
"Why don't you
just pay your wife?"

01:12.333 --> 01:14.335
I should charge him,
he should pay me,

01:14.335 --> 01:16.685
and the same dynamic
will exist.

01:16.685 --> 01:19.514
Well, it seemed like
a very good idea.

01:19.514 --> 01:21.298
He needs to
think of you as a whore,

01:21.298 --> 01:23.170
so why not charge him?

01:23.170 --> 01:24.780
- Yes, and it worked.
- Yeah.

01:24.780 --> 01:27.391
Paying her
was exciting,

01:27.391 --> 01:30.264
and it felt like
being with a hooker.

01:30.264 --> 01:32.309
Mm, mm, which
he finds naughty.

01:32.309 --> 01:33.571
And exciting.

01:33.571 --> 01:36.096
Sometimes
a creative solution...

01:36.096 --> 01:38.707
She started charging
too much.

01:38.707 --> 01:41.144
I am not a
low-class bimbo, okay?

01:41.144 --> 01:43.581
If I was
a professional,

01:43.581 --> 01:46.018
I would be
a high-class call girl.

01:46.018 --> 01:48.804
I'm not paying
my wife $700 a pop.

01:48.804 --> 01:50.806
- Christ, Lorna...
- Mm-hmm.

01:50.806 --> 01:53.896
Okay, for 700 bucks,

01:53.896 --> 01:56.681
I could get a fantastic
professional whore.

01:56.681 --> 01:58.509
Great, well, I'm not
doing it for 200 anymore.

01:58.509 --> 02:00.381
Why not?
It's fun money.

02:00.381 --> 02:02.992
I could get at least 500
on the open market.

02:02.992 --> 02:04.776
This is safer, and
you can work at home.

02:04.776 --> 02:06.038
Who cares?

02:06.038 --> 02:07.910
I really think
we can work this out.

02:07.910 --> 02:11.827
You know, it's really...
it's all in the family,

02:11.827 --> 02:15.091
and you could give him
maybe a little discount.

02:15.091 --> 02:18.094
I mean, he does
use you regularly.

02:18.094 --> 02:20.314
[male announcer] Meanwhile,
police have apprehended

02:20.314 --> 02:22.577
the other man
who escaped in San Francisco.

02:22.577 --> 02:25.362
He is Alvin Broadnax,
wanted in the bombing

02:25.362 --> 02:27.016
of the Seattle draft board

02:27.016 --> 02:29.149
and the shooting
of the state trooper.

02:29.149 --> 02:31.238
Broadnax had been
traced to New Jersey,

02:31.238 --> 02:32.587
where he was picked up in...

02:32.587 --> 02:35.198
Oh, Jesus, Kay,
the noose is tightening.

02:35.198 --> 02:36.199
[radio clicks off]

02:36.199 --> 02:37.200
- Well?
- God.

02:37.200 --> 02:39.071
Chairman Mao says that

02:39.071 --> 02:41.378
a calm heart
stills all panic.

02:41.378 --> 02:42.945
Screw Chairman Mao.

02:42.945 --> 02:44.947
You... you and I
will be in prison.

02:44.947 --> 02:48.124
Chairman Mao will be in
his palace eating spare ribs.

02:48.124 --> 02:49.560
Let me tell you something.

02:49.560 --> 02:50.996
If I wind up in prison,

02:50.996 --> 02:53.129
I am never gonna
take a shower.

02:53.129 --> 02:54.739
I can promise you
one thing,

02:54.739 --> 02:56.828
that she will not
be here long.

02:56.828 --> 02:59.918
Yeah, meanwhile, her
accomplice was captured.

02:59.918 --> 03:04.096
You know, thank God the guy
doesn't know where she is.

03:04.096 --> 03:06.534
Um, he... he does.

03:06.534 --> 03:08.188
What do you mean,
he does?

03:08.188 --> 03:09.580
[stammers]
How do you know he does?

03:09.580 --> 03:11.321
They've...
they've been in contact.

03:11.321 --> 03:13.758
Well, that's it.
I'm...

03:13.758 --> 03:15.717
You know, I'm leaving
for Cuba tonight.

03:15.717 --> 03:17.936
Oh, that's interesting
because so is she.

03:17.936 --> 03:20.461
Not tonight, but she is
planning to go to Cuba.

03:20.461 --> 03:22.071
You know,
she's delusional.

03:22.071 --> 03:23.507
She's gonna be caught,

03:23.507 --> 03:25.117
and then you know
what happens?

03:25.117 --> 03:26.728
Then she implicates us.

03:26.728 --> 03:28.120
[laughing]
Oh, Lenny?

03:28.120 --> 03:29.774
Lenny will never talk.

03:29.774 --> 03:31.428
She'll never talk?
Can I say...

03:31.428 --> 03:33.430
Can I say two words...
two words to you?

03:33.430 --> 03:34.605
- Uh-huh.
- Okay?

03:34.605 --> 03:35.954
- Yeah.
- Sodium Pentothal.

03:35.954 --> 03:37.391
They give her
an injection. [snaps]

03:37.391 --> 03:39.131
Next thing you know,
FBI's at our door

03:39.131 --> 03:40.742
with his-and-her
handcuffs.

03:40.742 --> 03:42.961
You know,
she's given us some

03:42.961 --> 03:45.312
very interesting
things to read.

03:45.312 --> 03:46.617
Like what?

03:46.617 --> 03:48.053
Well, like things

03:48.053 --> 03:50.055
that opened my eyes
to various things

03:50.055 --> 03:51.883
that my eyes had
been closed to.

03:51.883 --> 03:53.885
Well, to what? What are
we talking about here?

03:53.885 --> 03:57.062
Well, like the fact that
we go to cocktail parties,

03:57.062 --> 04:00.588
and we talk the talk,
but we never walk the walk.

04:00.588 --> 04:02.198
Yeah, well, I don't
want to walk the walk

04:02.198 --> 04:04.896
or shoot the shoot
or bomb the bomb.

04:06.855 --> 04:10.293
Okay, so you're going
straight to Manhattan, right?

04:10.293 --> 04:12.513
Right, right, right,
and I think I have...

04:12.513 --> 04:14.471
I'm sure I have all your
instructions just right.

04:14.471 --> 04:15.907
Don't worry
about a thing.

04:15.907 --> 04:17.517
I can't thank you
enough for doing this.

04:17.517 --> 04:19.694
Well, life is complicated.
Life is complicated.

04:19.694 --> 04:21.348
I've already... you know.

04:21.348 --> 04:23.175
It's so dangerous
for you and Sid,

04:23.175 --> 04:25.700
me staying here, and now
you're doing this for me.

04:25.700 --> 04:27.310
No, no, there
are black issues,

04:27.310 --> 04:28.920
as Chairman Mao says.

04:28.920 --> 04:30.966
There are white issues,
there are gray issues,

04:30.966 --> 04:34.404
and this is
all of those issues.

04:34.404 --> 04:36.798
Have you said anything
to your husband yet?

04:36.798 --> 04:39.017
No, he's going to go
to his cardiologist,

04:39.017 --> 04:41.455
and I don't want his heart
to stop before he gets there.

04:41.455 --> 04:43.239
Don't worry about it, really.
It's going to be okay.

04:43.239 --> 04:44.675
[car horn honks]

04:44.675 --> 04:46.286
- Thank you.
- It's gonna be great.

04:46.286 --> 04:49.289
[jazz music]

04:49.289 --> 04:57.035
♪ ♪

04:58.559 --> 04:59.995
There's nothing
wrong with you.

04:59.995 --> 05:02.519
You're absolutely fine.

05:02.519 --> 05:04.086
Your heart's good.

05:04.086 --> 05:05.783
You may have
a little indigestion,

05:05.783 --> 05:07.350
but that's all.

05:07.350 --> 05:08.873
And what about my lung?

05:10.527 --> 05:12.703
Well, the X-ray report
I got is negative,

05:12.703 --> 05:15.227
so you see, you're
really in good shape.

05:15.227 --> 05:17.360
I get the blood test
back in a few days.

05:17.360 --> 05:19.754
Are you anticipating
something?

05:19.754 --> 05:21.016
[doctor] No.

05:21.016 --> 05:22.931
Your last blood test
was normal.

05:22.931 --> 05:25.934
Yes, but that was...
that was when?

05:25.934 --> 05:29.024
Two weeks ago, at your
allergist's office.

05:30.765 --> 05:33.245
You know, I don't want
to be an alarmist,

05:33.245 --> 05:38.076
but I notice in my
right thumb... not a pain.

05:38.076 --> 05:41.384
It's not a pain, but
I have an awareness,

05:41.384 --> 05:44.561
an awareness in my right
thumb, and when I move

05:44.561 --> 05:48.217
the right thumb, what happens
is, I will experience

05:48.217 --> 05:51.394
a kind of disorientation,
a dizzy feeling,

05:51.394 --> 05:55.703
and... and maybe some
slight loss of appetite.

05:55.703 --> 05:59.924
I can't afford not to eat
because I can't lose weight,

05:59.924 --> 06:03.885
because I need the weight
to protect me against disease.

06:03.885 --> 06:05.582
What disease is that?

06:07.367 --> 06:11.414
Is there a possibility
that I could have malaria?

06:11.414 --> 06:15.113
I'll call you when
the blood work gets in.

06:15.113 --> 06:17.159
If you become aware
of your thumb, honey,

06:17.159 --> 06:20.292
we'll go straight
to the ER, really.

06:20.292 --> 06:21.990
So what are you saying?

06:21.990 --> 06:24.166
You're not gonna give me
anything for my thumb?

06:24.166 --> 06:26.951
We should all be so healthy.
[laughs]

06:26.951 --> 06:30.781
And as for
that ringing sound

06:30.781 --> 06:32.609
that you keep hearing
in your kneecap...

06:32.609 --> 06:33.828
Yes.

06:33.828 --> 06:35.656
...it's nothing,

06:35.656 --> 06:37.397
but I'm going to
keep my eye on it.

06:40.312 --> 06:41.531
See, I was right.

06:41.531 --> 06:42.750
It was chapped lips.

06:42.750 --> 06:45.013
It wasn't the
flesh-eating virus.

06:45.013 --> 06:48.625
Yes, but chapped lips, uh,
untreated, can be fatal,

06:48.625 --> 06:50.801
so... so now come on,
let's go have lunch.

06:50.801 --> 06:53.238
- What time is it?
- It's 1:00.

06:53.238 --> 06:54.675
- It's 1:00?
- Yeah, you know,

06:54.675 --> 06:56.285
you've asked me that
six times today.

06:56.285 --> 06:58.113
I don't understand.
Let's go have lunch.

06:58.113 --> 07:00.420
We'll relax. We'll get
a nice French meal.

07:00.420 --> 07:03.205
We'll... we'll go to
a nice restaurant.

07:03.205 --> 07:04.859
We can get some wine.

07:04.859 --> 07:07.427
We can get some
delicious food, you know?

07:07.427 --> 07:10.560
We don't have to worry
about going home early today

07:10.560 --> 07:13.607
and that crazy crackpot
who invaded the house.

07:13.607 --> 07:14.956
We don't have
to think about her.

07:14.956 --> 07:17.175
Darling, that sounds
just great, but first,

07:17.175 --> 07:19.134
I'd just like to run
down to Brooklyn, okay?

07:19.134 --> 07:20.265
Where?

07:20.265 --> 07:21.571
Brooklyn, I want
to go to 119...

07:21.571 --> 07:23.051
- Brooklyn?
- ...Veronica Street.

07:23.051 --> 07:24.661
Is that okay?
Just take a second.

07:24.661 --> 07:26.358
Well, what are we
gonna do in Brooklyn?

07:26.358 --> 07:28.143
I just have a little errand
to do. Really, it's nothing.

07:28.143 --> 07:30.058
What do you mean, an errand?
What kind of errand?

07:30.058 --> 07:32.016
I just have to pick something
up for a friend, okay?

07:32.016 --> 07:33.844
- Is that all right?
- In Brooklyn?

07:33.844 --> 07:35.672
It will take
a minute, yes, okay?

07:35.672 --> 07:37.500
Can you go after lunch?

07:37.500 --> 07:39.894
- I have to do it by 2:00.
- You must do it?

07:39.894 --> 07:41.765
I must do it
by 2:00, darling.

07:44.246 --> 07:46.248
What are you doing
down here, buying heroin?

07:46.248 --> 07:47.510
Oh, very funny.

07:47.510 --> 07:48.903
I mean, this is...
this is crazy.

07:48.903 --> 07:50.731
Where are we?
This is so desolate.

07:50.731 --> 07:52.646
So, wait, at 2:00...

07:52.646 --> 07:54.517
What's at 2:00?

07:54.517 --> 07:56.693
A man will come and
give us a briefcase.

07:56.693 --> 07:59.870
We're... you're buying
a new briefcase?

07:59.870 --> 08:02.699
Uh, not...
no, not exactly.

08:02.699 --> 08:04.919
Well, what?
I mean, you're so cryptic.

08:04.919 --> 08:06.529
I mean,
you drag me down here...

08:06.529 --> 08:09.184
Doing... doing
something for Lenny.

08:09.184 --> 08:11.403
Ah, now it becomes clear,
for Lenny.

08:11.403 --> 08:13.057
Yeah, but we're doing
something for Lenny

08:13.057 --> 08:14.581
so she can leave
tomorrow.

08:14.581 --> 08:16.583
Oh, that's fine, if
she's leaving tomorrow,

08:16.583 --> 08:19.455
then anything
you have to do is great.

08:20.935 --> 08:22.327
But it's nothing
dangerous, right?

08:22.327 --> 08:23.503
I mean...
[stammers]

08:23.503 --> 08:26.114
Has nothing to do
with guns or...

08:26.114 --> 08:27.724
No, she has a gun.

08:27.724 --> 08:28.899
Yeah, I know she...

08:28.899 --> 08:30.640
I remember
she's got a gun.

08:30.640 --> 08:33.251
Look, in for a penny,
in for a pound.

08:33.251 --> 08:34.948
I want my penny back.

08:34.948 --> 08:36.602
Well, it's too late now.

08:36.602 --> 08:38.648
Then keep it at
a penny, you know?

08:38.648 --> 08:40.432
The pound
is up to $1.80.

08:40.432 --> 08:42.390
I don't want
to be in for $1.80.

08:42.390 --> 08:44.131
[car engine growls]

08:46.438 --> 08:50.051
That's the Volkswagen;
that must be him.

08:50.051 --> 08:51.487
[percussive jazz music]

08:51.487 --> 08:53.097
[Sidney]
Oh, Jesus...

08:53.097 --> 08:55.535
[Kay] Uh, hi, Lenny said

08:55.535 --> 08:57.493
you had something for her
to give to us.

08:57.493 --> 08:59.800
Okay, okay, I just wanted to
make sure y'all was good people.

08:59.800 --> 09:00.888
Briefcase,
a briefcase.

09:00.888 --> 09:02.933
Yeah,
it's right here.

09:02.933 --> 09:04.369
I told you
it'd be a snap.

09:04.369 --> 09:06.067
Yeah well, snap faster.
This is treason.

09:06.067 --> 09:07.634
Hold it.
[briefcase thunks]

09:07.634 --> 09:09.636
- Ow!
- I just want you to know

09:09.636 --> 09:11.681
that we're proud of what
you're doing for America.

09:11.681 --> 09:13.727
Thank you. Now, listen,
you need to give that to...

09:13.727 --> 09:15.511
make sure you give that to...
[sirens wail]

09:15.511 --> 09:17.339
Oh, shit,
they followed me.

09:17.339 --> 09:18.993
Run, run!

09:18.993 --> 09:20.429
Oh, God!

09:20.429 --> 09:22.387
Well...
[stammers]

09:22.387 --> 09:23.824
- I... I...
- Police found you.

09:23.824 --> 09:27.479
In here, go in here.
[gate creaks]

09:27.479 --> 09:28.785
[sirens wail]
Come in here.

09:28.785 --> 09:30.787
Uh, Sid, this way.

09:30.787 --> 09:32.006
Where are you going?

09:32.006 --> 09:34.791
My heart, my heart.

09:34.791 --> 09:36.706
Your heart is fine;
you just had a checkup.

09:36.706 --> 09:38.839
Yeah, but the
blood work's not back.

09:38.839 --> 09:41.668
♪ ♪

09:41.668 --> 09:43.321
Come on.

09:43.321 --> 09:44.932
[Sidney]
Oh, Jesus.

09:44.932 --> 09:47.587
We're trapped.
We're trapped up here.

09:47.587 --> 09:49.284
We can jump.

09:49.284 --> 09:55.769
♪ ♪

09:55.769 --> 09:58.336
[Kay] Throw the briefcase
over to me.

09:58.336 --> 09:59.816
What?

09:59.816 --> 10:02.514
Throw the...[gasps]
throw the briefcase, Sid.

10:04.604 --> 10:05.822
[briefcase thunks]

10:05.822 --> 10:08.956
Good throw, now jump.

10:08.956 --> 10:11.523
Jump?

10:11.523 --> 10:15.092
I never jump anyplace
where there's gravity.

10:15.092 --> 10:16.311
Jump!

10:16.311 --> 10:21.316
♪ ♪

10:21.316 --> 10:23.492
[Sidney] Be careful, Kay,
this thing is wobbling.

10:23.492 --> 10:24.711
I know.

10:24.711 --> 10:25.929
You be careful.

10:25.929 --> 10:27.365
Hold on to that
briefcase, okay?

10:27.365 --> 10:28.758
- Steady.
- Okay.

10:28.758 --> 10:30.281
Oh, my God,
let me down here.

10:30.281 --> 10:31.239
[briefcase crashes open]

10:31.239 --> 10:32.719
Okay, this way.

10:32.719 --> 10:33.981
Ooh. Oh, Jesus.

10:33.981 --> 10:35.417
Oh, my God,
pick up the money.

10:35.417 --> 10:37.201
Okay, no.
What? Are you nuts?

10:37.201 --> 10:38.594
It's a fortune.

10:38.594 --> 10:40.248
Yes,
but it's Cuban.

10:40.248 --> 10:41.684
What's the difference?

10:41.684 --> 10:43.381
It's a clue.
Pick up the money.

10:43.381 --> 10:45.079
She's right.
It's a clue.

10:48.865 --> 10:50.388
Well,
I don't understand.

10:50.388 --> 10:52.303
Why do you want to
postpone the wedding?

10:52.303 --> 10:54.523
Out of fairness to you.

10:54.523 --> 10:56.046
Well, what does
that mean?

10:56.046 --> 10:58.005
I'm having
second thoughts

10:58.005 --> 11:00.007
about my life,
about my job.

11:00.007 --> 11:02.662
Well, your life
is finance,

11:02.662 --> 11:05.055
that's nothing
to be ashamed of.

11:05.055 --> 11:06.753
No, it's just...
I'm not so sure that I want

11:06.753 --> 11:10.887
to spend my life using
money to make more money.

11:10.887 --> 11:12.933
What? Do you have
a problem with money?

11:12.933 --> 11:15.109
No, not if it's
used properly.

11:15.109 --> 11:16.458
Meaning?

11:16.458 --> 11:18.068
Meaning that...
if it's used fairly,

11:18.068 --> 11:20.070
if, you know, the
masses aren't exploited.

11:20.070 --> 11:21.942
Well, you sound
like Karl Marx.

11:21.942 --> 11:24.335
Well, that's one of the
people I've been reading.

11:24.335 --> 11:25.902
Well, surely you're
not a Communist.

11:25.902 --> 11:27.208
No, I don't know
what I am.

11:27.208 --> 11:29.123
I know that I'm
for human decency.

11:29.123 --> 11:31.734
Well, suddenly you
have political ideas...

11:31.734 --> 11:33.344
and radical ones.
What happened to you?

11:33.344 --> 11:35.346
I'm just saying,
I've grown skeptical

11:35.346 --> 11:37.174
of passive resistance.

11:37.174 --> 11:39.786
So what are you
suggesting?

11:39.786 --> 11:41.309
The violent overthrow

11:41.309 --> 11:42.745
of the United States
government?

11:42.745 --> 11:46.749
No, no, I'm not...
I'm suggesting change.

11:46.749 --> 11:48.882
I'm for change;
I'm for, you know,

11:48.882 --> 11:50.710
not minuscule change
but meaningful change.

11:50.710 --> 11:52.102
You mean
radical change?

11:52.102 --> 11:53.625
By any means necessary.

11:56.672 --> 11:59.544
This is a you that
I don't recognize.

11:59.544 --> 12:02.722
Well, my personality
is evolving.

12:02.722 --> 12:04.636
Well, I think that this
may all be a way of you

12:04.636 --> 12:06.595
telling me that you
don't want to marry me.

12:06.595 --> 12:07.901
That's what I think.

12:09.990 --> 12:12.296
Jesus, Kay, this has been
the worst day of my life,

12:12.296 --> 12:13.950
and, you know,
it's still early.

12:13.950 --> 12:15.430
Here.

12:15.430 --> 12:17.040
Come on, you can put
some money in too.

12:17.040 --> 12:18.476
- Let's not quibble.
- Okay, okay.

12:18.476 --> 12:20.478
Here, take this. Okay.
Now, I think we did it.

12:20.478 --> 12:22.263
I think we made it.
I think we're safe.

12:22.263 --> 12:24.004
- All right.
- I don't think anyone's coming.

12:24.004 --> 12:25.309
Let's just close
this thing.

12:25.309 --> 12:27.137
God, we got
hot merchandise here.

12:27.137 --> 12:28.443
[tires squealing]

12:28.443 --> 12:29.618
- You know, this is...
- What?

12:29.618 --> 12:31.838
Is that a police car?

12:31.838 --> 12:33.491
- No.
- Don't scare me.

12:33.491 --> 12:34.754
You know I got an ulcer

12:34.754 --> 12:35.972
the size of
the Holland Tunnel.

12:35.972 --> 12:37.539
You don't have an ulcer.

12:37.539 --> 12:39.193
Don't tell me
I don't have an ulcer.

12:39.193 --> 12:40.977
Maybe they can't find it,
but I have an ulcer.

12:40.977 --> 12:42.152
Okay, I think
we're clear.

12:42.152 --> 12:43.545
Where are we going?

12:43.545 --> 12:45.155
We're going... going
to hand this off.

12:45.155 --> 12:46.722
To who?

12:46.722 --> 12:48.158
To a man, that's
all I know, to a man.

12:48.158 --> 12:50.770
Jesus, Kay, God's gonna
punish us for this.

12:50.770 --> 12:52.510
Oh, for God's sake.

12:52.510 --> 12:54.121
God's not gonna punish you;
you're an atheist.

12:54.121 --> 12:57.820
Yes, but if I'm wrong,
we're in big trouble.

12:57.820 --> 13:01.215
[Kay]
You see that phone booth?

13:01.215 --> 13:05.828
At 3:00, you will enter that
phone booth and make a call.

13:05.828 --> 13:07.264
To who?

13:07.264 --> 13:08.526
It doesn't matter.

13:08.526 --> 13:10.398
You're not going
to make a real call.

13:10.398 --> 13:13.183
You're going to pretend
to talk, pretend to dial,

13:13.183 --> 13:15.795
and then mime hanging up.

13:15.795 --> 13:17.884
And what is the point?

13:17.884 --> 13:19.494
You're going to leave
this briefcase

13:19.494 --> 13:21.365
in that phone booth.

13:21.365 --> 13:22.845
Uh-huh.

13:22.845 --> 13:25.413
And then a man is going
to come and make a call.

13:25.413 --> 13:28.155
A... a real call,
or will he mime it?

13:28.155 --> 13:29.939
It doesn't matter.

13:29.939 --> 13:32.115
The point is, he's going
to leave with the briefcase.

13:32.115 --> 13:34.552
Well, I can't wait
till that moment,

13:34.552 --> 13:36.076
when this briefcase
is gone,

13:36.076 --> 13:38.730
'cause this has been
nothing but trouble.

13:38.730 --> 13:41.429
Well, we're doing this so
that she can leave tomorrow.

13:41.429 --> 13:43.648
Yes, and the minute
she goes,

13:43.648 --> 13:46.869
I give a major donation
to the Red Cross.

13:46.869 --> 13:48.392
Well, she'll be gone.
[laughs]

13:48.392 --> 13:51.743
But you've got to admit,
it's been exciting.

13:51.743 --> 13:53.441
I don't know how
you could volunteer

13:53.441 --> 13:55.138
for something like this.

13:55.138 --> 13:58.315
Well, you know, we just
drag around in this,

13:58.315 --> 14:01.884
our everyday marriage,
and I just thought,

14:01.884 --> 14:04.669
you know, this is
something so different and...

14:04.669 --> 14:06.193
Yeah, 'cause, you know,
she gives you these books,

14:06.193 --> 14:09.109
and it fills your head
full of... you know?

14:09.109 --> 14:12.112
I'm glad she didn't
give you Mein Kampf.

14:12.112 --> 14:15.593
And then you give them
to your silly book club,

14:15.593 --> 14:18.205
and then these
ladies get crazy.

14:18.205 --> 14:19.684
You're in
pretty good shape.

14:19.684 --> 14:21.164
When you ran up
those stairs

14:21.164 --> 14:24.211
and you went leaping
over those roofs?

14:24.211 --> 14:26.082
Yeah, it's amazing what
the human body can do

14:26.082 --> 14:28.302
when it's being chased
by a policeman.

14:28.302 --> 14:30.347
It's 3:00, go.

14:30.347 --> 14:34.047
You know, you volunteered
for the thing,

14:34.047 --> 14:37.311
and all the dirty work,
I have to do.

14:37.311 --> 14:38.747
'Cause I'm the lookout.

14:38.747 --> 14:40.357
I have better ears
and better eyes,

14:40.357 --> 14:41.750
and... and I'm sharper.

14:41.750 --> 14:44.535
Yes, you should
put me in a home.

14:44.535 --> 14:46.189
Be right back.

14:46.189 --> 14:49.192
[upbeat jazz music]

