15:17.655 --> 15:20.702
Okay, now what?

15:20.702 --> 15:22.660
Now we wait until the man
comes to pick it up.

15:22.660 --> 15:24.314
Then we split.

15:24.314 --> 15:28.144
Yes, but, uh,
that's not a man,

15:28.144 --> 15:31.191
or he's in drag.

15:31.191 --> 15:33.367
[Kay] I'm pretty sure
she said a man.

15:33.367 --> 15:37.023
[Sidney] Well, that's not a man.
That's a woman.

15:37.023 --> 15:38.502
[Kay] It is a woman,
isn't it?

15:38.502 --> 15:40.069
Yes, it's a woman,
and she's...

15:40.069 --> 15:42.506
and she's picking it up.

15:42.506 --> 15:44.944
Well, let's...

15:44.944 --> 15:47.120
Maybe the plan
has been changed.

15:47.120 --> 15:49.557
Can you go back and just
very subtly try to find out

15:49.557 --> 15:51.951
whether that's the person
who's supposed to pick it up?

15:51.951 --> 15:53.126
How am I going
to find out?

15:53.126 --> 15:55.171
What are you
talking about?

15:55.171 --> 15:57.043
Maybe just take
the briefcase back.

15:57.043 --> 15:58.696
How am I gonna
get it back?

15:58.696 --> 16:01.308
Just say that you
left it there by mistake.

16:01.308 --> 16:02.962
It's a mistake,
and it's your package,

16:02.962 --> 16:04.441
and you want it back.
Come on.

16:04.441 --> 16:07.009
Jesus, you sit here with
these brilliant notions,

16:07.009 --> 16:08.619
and I carry them out.

16:08.619 --> 16:16.976
♪ ♪

16:16.976 --> 16:18.586
- Uh, excuse me, miss?
- Yeah?

16:18.586 --> 16:20.588
[stammering]
I left my... that's mine.

16:20.588 --> 16:21.763
I left it in there.

16:21.763 --> 16:23.634
How do I know that?

16:23.634 --> 16:27.073
Well, I'm telling you,
I left my... I was just...

16:27.073 --> 16:28.639
All I see is you
running out of a café.

16:28.639 --> 16:30.380
How do I know
that's yours?

16:30.380 --> 16:32.382
'Cause I'm telling you
it's my brief...

16:32.382 --> 16:33.775
[stammering]
I left it in there.

16:33.775 --> 16:35.081
Give me some proof.

16:35.081 --> 16:36.691
I don't know
that's yours.

16:36.691 --> 16:38.910
I'm telling you
it's my briefcase.

16:38.910 --> 16:40.738
- Believe me.
- No, this is not...

16:40.738 --> 16:42.131
this should go to
the lost and found.

16:42.131 --> 16:43.872
No, no, no, no,
it's mine.

16:43.872 --> 16:45.613
- I promise you it's mine.
- Don't grab it!

16:45.613 --> 16:47.223
- I'm not grabbing! I'm...
- You just grabbed it.

16:47.223 --> 16:48.616
I'm taking it.
I'm not grabbing it.

16:48.616 --> 16:50.270
Well, no... just...
[laughs]

16:50.270 --> 16:52.663
I... I understand that
you think this is yours,

16:52.663 --> 16:54.665
but I wouldn't fight with me,
if I were you, okay?

16:54.665 --> 16:56.493
I'm not fighting.
It's my brief...

16:56.493 --> 16:58.104
It's my briefcase.

16:58.104 --> 16:59.888
Don't grab it.
I'm doing the right thing.

16:59.888 --> 17:01.150
Officer!

17:01.150 --> 17:02.586
Don't, no,
it's not...

17:02.586 --> 17:04.109
This should go to
the lost and found.

17:04.109 --> 17:05.154
I went to make
a phone call.

17:05.154 --> 17:06.547
I find this briefcase.

17:06.547 --> 17:07.983
This man comes
running out of a café,

17:07.983 --> 17:09.550
telling me
it's his briefcase.

17:09.550 --> 17:11.421
- How do I know that?
- It's my briefcase.

17:11.421 --> 17:13.031
- Trying to do the right thing.
- It's my briefcase.

17:13.031 --> 17:14.642
- Okay, okay, okay.
- Thank you, Officer.

17:14.642 --> 17:16.035
Can you identify it?

17:16.035 --> 17:18.602
Can I...
yes, it's a briefcase.

17:18.602 --> 17:20.256
What's in it?

17:20.256 --> 17:21.474
What's in
the briefcase?

17:21.474 --> 17:23.085
Yeah, tell me,
and I'll check.

17:23.085 --> 17:25.740
Oh...
[stammers]

17:25.740 --> 17:28.743
You know, it's...
I don't...

17:28.743 --> 17:30.136
It's not really
my briefcase.

17:30.136 --> 17:31.572
So I was kidding.
[laughs]

17:31.572 --> 17:32.703
Ah, yeah, yeah,
yeah, okay.

17:32.703 --> 17:34.140
What's your name?

17:34.140 --> 17:36.533
Muntzinger, Sidney.
S.J. Muntzinger.

17:36.533 --> 17:38.361
Perhaps you've read
some of my books.

17:38.361 --> 17:39.580
[stammers]

17:39.580 --> 17:41.582
The S is for Sidney,
the J...

17:41.582 --> 17:43.192
I just put that in
for prestige,

17:43.192 --> 17:44.411
like Harry S. Truman.

17:44.411 --> 17:46.282
Let me tell you
something.

17:46.282 --> 17:48.241
Claiming that this
was yours

17:48.241 --> 17:50.112
was not a very nice
thing to do.

17:50.112 --> 17:53.333
Oh, I'm
a congenital liar.

17:53.333 --> 17:56.292
My family, it's in
the genes, we...

17:56.292 --> 17:57.728
Okay, good,
you know what?

17:57.728 --> 17:59.165
Move along now,
or I'm gonna have to

17:59.165 --> 18:00.775
arrest you for
attempted theft, okay?

18:00.775 --> 18:02.211
Put me down
for two tickets

18:02.211 --> 18:04.213
to the Policeman-Fireman
Tug of War.

18:04.213 --> 18:05.432
It's my favorite event.

18:05.432 --> 18:07.434
Okay, all right,
thank you.

18:07.434 --> 18:08.957
- Have a good day.
- Thank you, Officer.

18:08.957 --> 18:10.089
You got it.

18:17.183 --> 18:19.185
Hey.

18:19.185 --> 18:20.795
Hey.

18:20.795 --> 18:22.449
Where you off to?

18:22.449 --> 18:25.060
I was never very good
at reading a map.

18:25.060 --> 18:26.975
Ah, of where?

18:29.151 --> 18:31.632
Upstate New York.

18:31.632 --> 18:34.330
Hmm, so I guess
you're really going.

18:35.592 --> 18:37.246
I have no choice.

18:37.246 --> 18:38.943
Well, I'm gonna
be sad to see you go.

18:42.295 --> 18:43.818
I can't stay here.

18:45.776 --> 18:47.517
So what is it?

18:47.517 --> 18:49.563
Canada, Cuba?

18:49.563 --> 18:50.868
Cuba.

18:52.696 --> 18:54.872
And suppose
I went with you?

18:54.872 --> 18:56.787
It's not a good idea.

18:56.787 --> 19:00.008
Why?
Think about it.

19:00.008 --> 19:02.837
Get to know each other
under the Caribbean moon.

19:02.837 --> 19:04.839
Oh, snap out of it,
come on.

19:04.839 --> 19:08.016
I'm on the run, and
you're getting married.

19:08.016 --> 19:11.889
I'm a devoted revolutionary,
and until this world

19:11.889 --> 19:14.457
changes for the better,
my fight goes on.

19:14.457 --> 19:16.285
Me too now.

19:16.285 --> 19:19.288
What the hell
would you do in Cuba?

19:19.288 --> 19:22.465
We'd work together to make
the world a better place.

19:22.465 --> 19:24.685
We could...
It's not like here.

19:24.685 --> 19:25.903
Things are much cheaper.

19:25.903 --> 19:27.688
We could find a way
to get by.

19:27.688 --> 19:29.298
You'd end up
waiting tables.

19:29.298 --> 19:30.865
Is that what you want?

19:30.865 --> 19:32.867
Yes, if I had to,
I would.

19:32.867 --> 19:34.695
And meanwhile,
I'd work to organize

19:34.695 --> 19:36.523
an agricultural collective.

19:36.523 --> 19:38.916
You couldn't work at
an agricultural collective

19:38.916 --> 19:41.354
if they gave you
seeds and a shovel.

19:41.354 --> 19:44.183
Do you know how long
you'd last in Cuba?

19:44.183 --> 19:46.576
I know
I'm in love with you.

19:46.576 --> 19:48.578
Forget it.

19:48.578 --> 19:50.145
Tomorrow,
I'm out of here.

19:50.145 --> 19:53.148
[lively jazz music]

19:53.148 --> 19:59.981
♪ ♪

19:59.981 --> 20:01.635
[Kay]
Oh...

20:01.635 --> 20:04.464
God, Sid.

20:04.464 --> 20:08.685
Sid, we...
you lost all her money.

20:08.685 --> 20:11.297
What do you mean
I lost all her money?

20:11.297 --> 20:12.776
What did you
expect me to do?

20:12.776 --> 20:15.214
Open the briefcase
with the cop there?

20:15.214 --> 20:17.172
Yes, Officer,
I always carry around

20:17.172 --> 20:19.609
$30,000 in Cuban money

20:19.609 --> 20:21.437
in case I want to buy
black bean soup.

20:25.180 --> 20:26.616
Were you able
to do it?

20:26.616 --> 20:28.052
[Kay] Uh... uh...

20:28.052 --> 20:29.445
You did transfer
the money, right?

20:29.445 --> 20:30.968
Nothing went wrong?

20:30.968 --> 20:32.535
Well, yes, one small
thing went wrong.

20:32.535 --> 20:33.754
Everything.

20:33.754 --> 20:36.060
What?
I was counting on this.

20:36.060 --> 20:38.106
Well, don't count on it.
Do it yourself.

20:38.106 --> 20:40.543
For God's sake, we're not
professional criminals.

20:40.543 --> 20:42.328
You know,
I'm writing a sitcom.

20:42.328 --> 20:43.633
It was our first time

20:43.633 --> 20:45.287
jumping from rooftop
to rooftop.

20:45.287 --> 20:47.681
Christ, she comes in here
full of, you know,

20:47.681 --> 20:51.728
half-baked ideas about
Fidel and... and Che

20:51.728 --> 20:54.427
and... and the great
Chairman Mao, you know,

20:54.427 --> 20:56.429
one of the few
overweight Chinese.

20:56.429 --> 20:58.387
[Kay] It was a simple
pick up and drop.

20:58.387 --> 20:59.823
It was supposed to be.

20:59.823 --> 21:02.043
Yeah, very simple,
except, the guy

21:02.043 --> 21:04.001
making the pickup was
followed by the police.

21:04.001 --> 21:05.742
[Lenny] What?

21:05.742 --> 21:07.918
[Kay] I think they're
closing in on us, Lenny.

21:07.918 --> 21:10.921
They got a pretty
good look at Sid.

21:10.921 --> 21:12.401
You didn't
tell me that.

21:12.401 --> 21:14.577
I didn't want
to worry you.

21:14.577 --> 21:18.189
Jesus Christ, you know,
you're jumping around the roof

21:18.189 --> 21:21.497
like Batman, and she's
safe up in her room

21:21.497 --> 21:25.675
reading Spartacusand coming
to all the wrong conclusions.

21:25.675 --> 21:27.808
That money
was for my escape.

21:27.808 --> 21:32.160
Hey, this is not how I want
to spend my golden years.

21:32.160 --> 21:33.727
Look, I know
they're closing in on us,

21:33.727 --> 21:36.207
but we have
a little bit of time.

21:36.207 --> 21:38.819
I just... I have to
keep a low profile...

21:38.819 --> 21:40.255
[muffled crashing, booming]

21:40.255 --> 21:42.083
[Kay] What was that?
- Jesus.

21:42.083 --> 21:44.346
God, I told Allen
not to make a bomb

21:44.346 --> 21:46.740
without me there.

21:46.740 --> 21:49.743
[upbeat jazzy music]

